1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:04,357
Combine the method into one High-Quality Collaboration Turn Checklist.

2
00:00:04,307 --> 00:00:09,201
It has five passes: Goal, Gaps, Grounds, Test, and Owner.

3
00:00:09,201 --> 00:00:13,759
Use it whenever an AI output looks ready enough to tempt immediate acceptance.

4
00:00:13,759 --> 00:00:15,403
Pass one is Goal.

5
00:00:15,403 --> 00:00:20,423
Write the intended decision, audience, and acceptance criteria beside the output.

6
00:00:20,423 --> 00:00:24,990
Mark any section that does not help that goal or that quietly changes the scope.

7
00:00:24,990 --> 00:00:26,778
Pass two is Gaps.

8
00:00:26,778 --> 00:00:32,250
List missing inputs, inferred assumptions, unresolved conflicts, and uncertainty.

9
00:00:32,250 --> 00:00:38,865
Ask the AI which missing item is most likely to change the result, then obtain that input or preserve the limitation.

10
00:00:38,865 --> 00:00:40,846
Pass three is Grounds.

11
00:00:40,846 --> 00:00:46,298
Trace important claims to evidence, calculations, rules, or observable behavior.

12
00:00:46,298 --> 00:00:50,721
Distinguish what the source establishes from what the AI or reviewer infers.

13
00:00:50,721 --> 00:00:53,500
Confidence must be earned claim by claim.

14
00:00:53,500 --> 00:00:55,336
Pass four is Test.

15
00:00:55,336 --> 00:00:58,980
Exercise the deliverable in the environment where it will be used.

16
00:00:58,980 --> 00:01:03,836
Run, compare, sample, simulate, or review it with the affected people.

17
00:01:03,836 --> 00:01:09,298
A functional-looking artifact becomes trustworthy only after relevant failure modes have been tried.

18
00:01:09,298 --> 00:01:11,057
Pass five is Owner.

19
00:01:11,057 --> 00:01:17,461
Record who accepts the remaining risk, who can approve release, and what signal would require rollback or revision.

20
00:01:17,461 --> 00:01:21,951
The checklist ends with a decision, not with another request for prettier wording.

21
00:01:21,951 --> 00:01:25,875
First, check Goal and Gaps before refining the presentation.

22
00:01:25,875 --> 00:01:29,644
Second, check Grounds and Test before trusting the result.

23
00:01:29,644 --> 00:01:34,329
Third, finish with an Owner who can accept, revise, or stop the work.
